org.orgName: The District Court of the United States, Western District of Washington, Northern Division

div1.p: In the United States District Court for the Western District of Washington, Northern Division
In the matter of the application of TSUNETARO MACHIDA for a writ of habeas corpus.

This matter having come on for hearing on motion of the Petitioner for an order for the withdrawal of bail deposited herein, and it appearing to the court that said petitioner has submitted himself to and now is in the custody of the commissioner of Immigration at Seattle, Washington; Now, therefore,
IT IS ORDERED that the petitioner may withdraw any and all bail heretofore deposited herein and that his bond filed herein be and it hereby is exonerated.
Done in open court this 21 day of September, 1922.
Alien Surrendered to U.S. Immigration at Seattle, Wash.,
